Package: mstATA
Title: Automated Test Assembly for Multistage Tests Using Mixed-Integer Linear Programming
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Hong","Chen", email="hongchen030@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides sparse, mixed-integer linear programming (MILP) model
    builders and solvers for automated test assembly (ATA) in multistage tests.
    Supports bottom-up, top-down, and hybrid strategies; enemy exclusions (enemy items, enemy stimuli); stimulus all-in/all-out or
    partial selection; item-usage control; single objective or multiple 
    objectives (weighted-sum, capped-maximin, maximin,goal programming and minimax); diagnosis of infeasible optimization models and their reformulation to resolve infeasibility through systematic identification of its causes.
